Variance Explained

ggplot(var_df, aes(x = PC, y = VarianceExplained, fill = factor(PC))) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity") +
  geom_text(aes(label = sprintf("%.2f%%", VarianceExplained * 100)), vjust = -0.5) +
  scale_fill_discrete(name = "PC") +
  labs(title = "Variance Explained by Principal Components", x = "Principal Component", y = "Proportion of Variance Explained") +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(
    plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5)
  ) +
  annotate("text", x = length(variance_explained), y = max(variance_explained), 
           label = sprintf("PC1 and PC2 explain %.2f%% of the total variance", cumulative_pc1_pc2), 
           hjust = 0.85, vjust = 1, size = 3.5, fontface = "bold.italic", color = "black")
